  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Randomized controlled single blind prospective comparative study
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study is intended to be a randomized controlled single blind prospective comparative
      study conducted to compare the efficacy of three monthly doses of sulphadoxine-pyrimethamine
      as intermittent preventive therapy for malaria with azithromycin in HIV positive pregnant
      women
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
